<paragraph id="317F36AF3625FC06C482DB20FB81B3B0" blockId="28.[178,1086,1244,1589]" lastBlockId="29.[178,1085,218,541]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="394" pageId="28" pageNumber="393">
Comment: The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3625FC07C6B8DB20FCA3B438" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1914" box="[648,780,1567,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanica">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3625FC07C6B8DB20FCA3B438" box="[648,780,1567,1589]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="393">O. hispanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a larger number (&quot;in grösserer Anzahl&quot;) of 
<typeStatus id="EE7B880D3624FC06C5F7DDE4FD8FB2FD" box="[455,544,219,240]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">syntypes</typeStatus>
from &quot;Nordspanien (Palencia)&quot; and few specimens (&quot;einzelne Stücke&quot;) from &quot;Navacenada&quot; and &quot;Badajoz&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="55514B5E3624FC06C71BDDC7FC5FB303" author="BERNHAUER M" box="[811,1008,248,270]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394" pagination="33 - 45" refId="ref20248" refString="BERNHAUER M. (1914): Beitrage zur Kenntnis der palaarktischen Staphyliniden-Fauna. III. - Munchener Koleopterologische Zeitwschrift 4: 33 - 45." type="journal article" year="1914">BERNHAUER 1914</bibRefCitation>
). Nine 
<typeStatus id="EE7B880D3624FC06C482DC29FEA4B326" box="[178,267,278,299]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">syntypes</typeStatus>
from Palencia were located in the Bernhauer collection at the FMNH; one of the males is designated as the 
<typeStatus id="EE7B880D3624FC06C633DC0DFDCCB345" box="[515,611,306,328]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The species is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3624FC06C7FFDC0CFE92B368" authority="ASSING 2008" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virgata">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3624FC06C7FFDC0CFB92B345" box="[975,1085,307,328]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">O. virgata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="55514B5E3624FC06C482DC70FE92B368" author="ASSING V" box="[178,317,335,357]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394" pagination="1301 - 1325" refId="ref19990" refString="ASSING V. (2008): Nine new species and additional records of Staphylinidae from southern Spain, with new synonymies (Insecta: Coleoptera). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 40 (2): 1301 - 1325." type="journal article" year="2008">ASSING 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, whose description is based on numerous specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="F304F84D3624FC06C797DC70FE2CB38E" isEnumeration="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">Andalucía and Castilla-La Mancha</collectingRegion>
; hence the synonymy proposed above. For an illustration of the median lobe of the aedeagus and the spermatheca of the 
<typeStatus id="EE7B880D3624FC06C737DCB5FCCBB3AD" box="[775,868,394,416]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">lectotype</typeStatus>
and a 
<typeStatus id="EE7B880D3624FC06C79EDCB5FB96B3AD" box="[942,1081,394,416]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">paralectotype</typeStatus>
, respectively, see 
<figureCitation id="A9FB2A2A3624FC06C550DC98FE7FB3B0" box="[352,464,423,445]" captionStart="Figs 42-50" captionStartId="26.[178,218,1463,1483]" captionTargetBox="[184,1080,298,1442]" captionTargetId="figure-113@26.[178,1085,283,1451]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 42-50: Oxypoda determinata SCRIBA (42-43; 42: neotype of O. determinata and lectotype of O. incerta EPPELSHEIM; 43: paralectotype of O. incerta), O. hispanica BERNHAUER (44-45; 44: lectotype; 45: paralectotype), and O. flavicornis KRAATZ (46-50) from Sicily (46-47), northern Anatolia (48), and Albania (49-50): (42, 44, 46-49) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (43, 45, 50) spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5327465" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5327465/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">Figs 44-45</figureCitation>
. The aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3624FC06C6B6DC97FD41B3B0" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2008" box="[646,750,424,445]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virgata">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3624FC06C6B6DC97FD41B3B0" box="[646,750,424,445]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">O. virgata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="55514B5E3624FC06C7A1DC98FB85B3B0" author="ASSING V" box="[913,1066,423,445]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394" pagination="1301 - 1325" refId="ref19990" refString="ASSING V. (2008): Nine new species and additional records of Staphylinidae from southern Spain, with new synonymies (Insecta: Coleoptera). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 40 (2): 1301 - 1325." type="journal article" year="2008">ASSING (2008)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="317F36AF3624FC06C482DCF2FD8BB010" blockId="29.[178,1085,218,541]" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicName id="F6C04D2C3624FC06C482DCF2FED4B3EE" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1914" box="[178,379,461,483]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oxypoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanica">
<emphasis id="03B4EABD3624FC06C482DCF2FED4B3EE" box="[178,379,461,483]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">Oxypoda hispanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been recorded only from 
<collectingCountry id="49D7763F3624FC06C6FDDCF2FCA6B3EE" box="[717,777,461,483]" name="Spain" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">Spain</collectingCountry>
, where it is widespread and apparently not particularly rare. The above specimens from the Haut Atlas represent the first records from 
<collectingCountry id="49D7763F3624FC06C559DF37FE6BB010" box="[361,452,520,541]" name="Morocco" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="A9FB2A2A3624FC06C5E2DF38FDB9B010" box="[466,534,519,541]" captionStart="Map 5" captionStartId="28.[178,223,1143,1163]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,408,1129]" captionTargetId="figure-312@28.[178,1085,408,1129]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Map 5: Distribution of Oxypoda hispanica BERNHAUER based on revised records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6483841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6483841/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="394">Map 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
